analysis: The documents all concern actions related to land management and resource allocation. They address topics such as coastal and marine spatial planning, counterterrorism efforts, support for Hispanic-Serving Institutions, energy exploration on the Outer Continental Shelf, civil service rules for the Government Printing Office, environmental justice, national forest boundaries, and transportation of household goods for military personnel. The sentiment is generally neutral, focusing on policy implementation and administrative procedures.
title: Federal Land and Resource Management Directives
